CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 20, 1958, pg. 16 reads: "Back In Action - Pittsburgher Dave Cook, leader of his own jazz quintet and currently headlining at the Crawford Grill, also has several engagements lined up for fraternity dances in area colleges. Cook, just two months out of the armed services, were he performed with the 327th Army Band, Baltimore, is an ex-pre-medical student, and composes and arranges for the group. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Dave Cook playing the Deagan Vibraharp
